Attribute VB_Name = "M_STATS_PROBDIST_NORMALFAMILY"

Option Explicit

'==============================================================================
' M_STATS_PROBDIST_NORMALFAMILY
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Provides robust normal-family probability distribution functions for
'   worksheet formulas, VBA models and Monte Carlo engines.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   The normal distribution is the core distribution used in Black-Scholes,
'   value-at-risk examples, regression diagnostics, Gaussian copulas and Monte
'   Carlo simulation. The lognormal distribution is the natural companion for
'   positive variables generated by geometric Brownian motion, including equity
'   prices and other strictly positive market factors.
'
'   Native Excel worksheet functions cover most of these distributions
'   (see WORKSHEET EQUIVALENTS below), but they are awkward to call from VBA:
'   Application.WorksheetFunction raises a trappable runtime error on bad input
'   instead of returning CVErr, and carries per-call marshalling overhead. This
'   module gives a single, VBA-native, consistently-validated surface that is
'   equally callable from a cell and from a tight numerical loop, plus helpers
'   that have no native equivalent at all.
'
' PUBLIC FUNCTIONS
'   Standard normal:
'     - K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density
'     - K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative
'     - K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative
'     - K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability
'     - K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast
'
'   General normal:
'     - K_STATS_Normal_Density
'     - K_STATS_Normal_Cumulative
'     - K_STATS_Normal_InverseCumulative
'     - K_STATS_Normal_ZScore
'     - K_STATS_Normal_IntervalProbability
'
'   Lognormal:
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_Density
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_Cumulative
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_InverseCumulative
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_Mean
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_Variance
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_StdDev
'     - K_STATS_Lognormal_ParametersFromMeanStdDev
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENTS (native Excel, 2010+ unless noted)
'   K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density              NORM.S.DIST(z, FALSE)
'   K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative           NORM.S.DIST(z, TRUE)   [legacy NORMSDIST]
'   K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative    NORM.S.INV(p)          [legacy NORMSINV]
'   K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability  NORM.S.DIST(b,TRUE) - NORM.S.DIST(a,TRUE)
'   K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast (none - numeric helper)
'   K_STATS_Normal_Density                      NORM.DIST(x, m, s, FALSE)
'   K_STATS_Normal_Cumulative                   NORM.DIST(x, m, s, TRUE)
'   K_STATS_Normal_InverseCumulative            NORM.INV(p, m, s)
'   K_STATS_Normal_ZScore                       STANDARDIZE(x, m, s)
'   K_STATS_Normal_IntervalProbability          NORM.DIST(b,m,s,TRUE) - NORM.DIST(a,m,s,TRUE)
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_Density                   LOGNORM.DIST(x, m, s, FALSE)
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_Cumulative                LOGNORM.DIST(x, m, s, TRUE) [legacy LOGNORMDIST, cumulative only]
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_InverseCumulative         LOGNORM.INV(p, m, s)        [legacy LOGINV]
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_Mean                      (none - use EXP(m + 0.5*s^2))
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_Variance                  (none)
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_StdDev                    (none - SQRT of lognormal variance)
'   K_STATS_Lognormal_ParametersFromMeanStdDev  (none - custom method-of-moments)
'
' ALGORITHM PROVENANCE
'   - Standard normal CDF (PROB_NormalCDF):
'       Hart rational/continued-fraction approximation (Hart et al.,
'       "Computer Approximations", 1968), in the double-precision arrangement
'       popularised by Graeme West, "Better Approximations to Cumulative Normal
'       Functions" (Wilmott Magazine, 2009). Public, published; not proprietary.
'       Accurate to approximately 1E-15.
'   - Inverse standard normal (PROB_NormalInvCDF):
'       Peter J. Acklam's rational approximation (released freely for any use by
'       the author), taken from the shared kernel PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw in
'       M_STATS_CORE and refined here with a single Halley iteration. Raw Acklam
'       alone is accurate to ~1.15E-9 relative; the Halley step lifts the central
'       region to ~5E-16. In the tail the Halley step is bounded by the RELATIVE
'       accuracy of PROB_NormalCDF (about 1E-10 past z = 7.07), and beyond
'       z = 37 it is skipped entirely because the CDF has saturated. Public.
'   - Lognormal moment and parameter formulas:
'       Standard closed-form textbook results (method of moments). Not proprietary.
'   The raw Acklam kernel lives in M_STATS_CORE as PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw, because
'   the Student t quantile seeds off it too. Only the Halley refinement, which is
'   normal-family-specific, remains here.
'   Nothing in this module is a newly-invented algorithm; the design/packaging,
'   validation policy and the fast Double contract are the local contribution.
'
' DESIGN PRINCIPLES
'   - Public worksheet-facing functions return Variant so they can return CVErr.
'   - Private numerical kernels return Double and avoid worksheet-facing overhead.
'   - The fast inverse-normal routine is exposed for Monte Carlo engines and
'     deliberately uses the raw (unrefined) Acklam kernel for speed.
'   - Invalid domains fail explicitly; they are not silently repaired.
'   - Overflow fails explicitly: a computation that would exceed Double range
'     returns CVErr(xlErrNum) rather than a clamped sentinel value.
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Invalid numeric domains return CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Overflow of an exponential result returns CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Unexpected runtime errors return CVErr(xlErrValue).
'   - Detailed diagnostic messages are written to Status; the Excel status bar
'     is updated only when PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR is True (default False).
'   - No MsgBox is raised.
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - M_STATS_CORE
'       Constants  : PROB_EPS, PROB_DOUBLE_MAX, PROB_MAX_EXP, PROB_MIN_EXP,
'                    PROB_LARGE_NUMBER, PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR
'       Predicates : PROB_IsFinite, PROB_IsValidProbabilityOpen
'       Primitives : PROB_TryExp, PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw
'       Diagnostics: PROB_SetStatus
'
' NOTES
'   - Lognormal parameters are the mean and standard deviation of Log(X), not of X.
'   - K_STATS_Lognormal_ParametersFromMeanStdDev converts arithmetic mean and standard
'     deviation into log-space parameters; both inputs must be strictly positive.
'   - K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast intentionally clips probabilities at
'     the endpoints and returns Double; use it only for validated numerical callers.
'   - Overflow policy: PROB_TryExp fails (returns False) when Exp would overflow a
'     Double. The lognormal Mean, Variance, StdDev and InverseCumulative routines
'     translate that into CVErr(xlErrNum). Underflow of an exponential is a valid
'     zero, not an error.
'   - Status-bar writes: gated behind PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR (default False).
'     Status-bar writes from a worksheet UDF are unreliable and add churn when a
'     function is bulk-filled; the ByRef Status argument is always populated and
'     is the intended diagnostic channel.
'   - VBA's And and Or are not short-circuit: both operands are always evaluated.
'     Any guard whose right operand can fault (a division, a Log of a non-positive
'     number) must be nested, never And-ed. See K_STATS_Lognormal_Variance and
'     K_STATS_Lognormal_StdDev.
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-09
'==============================================================================

'==============================================================================
' PRIVATE CONSTANTS
'==============================================================================

' Shared constants (PROB_EPS, PROB_MAX_EXP, PROB_MIN_EXP, PROB_LARGE_NUMBER,
' PROB_DOUBLE_MAX, PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR) now live in M_STATS_CORE. Only the
' normal-family-specific constants remain here. PROB_PI and PROB_TWO_PI were
' declared but never referenced and have been dropped.

Private Const PROB_SQRT_TWO_PI         As Double = 2.506628274631       'Sqr(2 * Pi), correctly rounded
Private Const PROB_INV_SQRT_TWO_PI     As Double = 0.398942280401433    '1 / Sqr(2 * Pi), correctly rounded
Private Const PROB_PDF_TAIL_CUTOFF     As Double = 38#               'Abs(Z) beyond which the density underflows to 0
Private Const PROB_CDF_TAIL_CUTOFF     As Double = 37#               'Abs(Z) beyond which the CDF saturates to 0/1
Private Const PROB_CDF_SPLIT           As Double = 7.07106781186547  'Sqr(50): rational vs continued-fraction split





Public Function K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density( _
    ByVal Z As Double, _
    Optional ByRef Status As String = "") _
    As Variant
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns the standard normal probability density function at Z.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   The standard normal density is used in option Greeks, likelihood examples,
'   regression diagnostics and probability-distribution teaching worksheets.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   NORM.S.DIST(Z, FALSE)  (Excel 2010+). This VBA form is CVErr-clean and
'   directly callable from numerical code.
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Closed-form standard normal density. Not proprietary.
'
' INPUTS
'   Z
'     Standard-normal variate.
'
'   Status
'     Optional ByRef diagnostic message.
'     Empty on success.
'     Populated on failure.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double density value.
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates that Z is finite.
'   - Returns Exp(-0.5 * Z^2) / Sqr(2 * Pi).
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Non-finite inputs return CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Unexpected runtime errors return CVErr(xlErrValue).
'   - Detailed diagnostic messages are written to Status (status bar only when
'     PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR is True).
'   - No MsgBox is raised.
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - PROB_IsFinite
'   - PROB_NormalPDF
'   - PROB_SetStatus
'
' CALLED FROM
'   - Excel worksheet formulas
'   - VBA callers
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-08
'==============================================================================
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' DECLARE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Dim FailMsg             As String          'Detailed failure message

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' INITIALIZE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Route unexpected runtime errors to the error handler
        On Error GoTo Err_Handler
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Initialize the failure message buffer
        FailMsg = vbNullString

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VALIDATE INPUTS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Validate finite input
        If Not PROB_IsFinite(Z) Then
            FailMsg = "Z must be a finite number"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' COMPUTE DENSITY
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Return standard normal density
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density = PROB_NormalPDF(Z)

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' RETURN SUCCESS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Exit before failure and error-handler blocks
        Exit Function

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' FAIL - NUMERIC
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fail_Num:
    'Write diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, FailMsg
    'Return worksheet numeric error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density = CVErr(xlErrNum)
    'Exit before the error handler
        Exit Function

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ERROR HANDLER
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Err_Handler:
    'Write unexpected runtime errors to diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, "Unexpected error in K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density: " & Err.Description
    'Return worksheet value error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Density = CVErr(xlErrValue)

End Function


Public Function K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative( _
    ByVal Z As Double, _
    Optional ByRef Status As String = "") _
    As Variant
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns the standard normal cumulative distribution function at Z.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   The standard normal cumulative distribution is a core building block for
'   Black-Scholes formulas, Gaussian risk-factor models and probability examples.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   NORM.S.DIST(Z, TRUE)  (Excel 2010+); legacy NORMSDIST(Z).
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Hart rational/continued-fraction approximation (Hart 1968) in the
'   double-precision arrangement popularised by Graeme West (Wilmott, 2009).
'   Public; accurate to ~1E-15.
'
' INPUTS
'   Z
'     Standard-normal variate.
'
'   Status
'     Optional ByRef diagnostic message.
'     Empty on success.
'     Populated on failure.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double cumulative probability.
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates that Z is finite.
'   - Computes the cumulative probability using a double-precision rational
'     approximation.
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Non-finite inputs return CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Unexpected runtime errors return CVErr(xlErrValue).
'   - Detailed diagnostic messages are written to Status (status bar only when
'     PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR is True).
'   - No MsgBox is raised.
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - PROB_IsFinite
'   - PROB_NormalCDF
'   - PROB_SetStatus
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-08
'==============================================================================
'

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' DECLARE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Dim FailMsg             As String          'Detailed failure message

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' INITIALIZE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Route unexpected runtime errors to the error handler
        On Error GoTo Err_Handler
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Initialize the failure message buffer
        FailMsg = vbNullString

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VALIDATE INPUTS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Validate finite input
        If Not PROB_IsFinite(Z) Then
            FailMsg = "Z must be a finite number"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' COMPUTE CUMULATIVE PROBABILITY
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Return standard normal cumulative probability
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative = PROB_NormalCDF(Z)

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' RETURN SUCCESS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Exit before failure and error-handler blocks
        Exit Function

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' FAIL - NUMERIC
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fail_Num:
    'Write diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, FailMsg
    'Return worksheet numeric error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative = CVErr(xlErrNum)
    'Exit before the error handler
        Exit Function

'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ERROR HANDLER
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Err_Handler:
    'Write unexpected runtime errors to diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, "Unexpected error in K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative: " & Err.Description
    'Return worksheet value error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_Cumulative = CVErr(xlErrValue)
End Function


Public Function K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative( _
    ByVal Probability As Double, _
    Optional ByRef Status As String = "") _
    As Variant
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns the inverse standard normal cumulative distribution function.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   The inverse standard normal is used to convert probabilities into normal
'   quantiles, for example in VaR, scenario generation and Monte Carlo shocks.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   NORM.S.INV(Probability)  (Excel 2010+); legacy NORMSINV(Probability).
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Peter J. Acklam's rational approximation (public, released freely) with a
'   single Halley refinement step. Accurate to ~1E-15.
'
' INPUTS
'   Probability
'     Probability level.
'     Must be strictly between 0 and 1.
'
'   Status
'     Optional ByRef diagnostic message.
'     Empty on success.
'     Populated on failure.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double standard-normal quantile.
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates that Probability is finite and strictly inside (0, 1).
'   - Uses Acklam's rational approximation refined by one Halley iteration.
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Invalid probabilities return CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Unexpected runtime errors return CVErr(xlErrValue).
'   - Detailed diagnostic messages are written to Status (status bar only when
'     PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR is True).
'   - No MsgBox is raised.
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - PROB_IsValidProbabilityOpen
'   - PROB_NormalInvCDF
'   - PROB_SetStatus
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-08
'==============================================================================
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' DECLARE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Dim FailMsg             As String          'Detailed failure message
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' INITIALIZE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Route unexpected runtime errors to the error handler
        On Error GoTo Err_Handler
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Initialize the failure message buffer
        FailMsg = vbNullString
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VALIDATE INPUTS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Validate probability domain
        If Not PROB_IsValidProbabilityOpen(Probability) Then
            FailMsg = "Probability must be strictly between 0 and 1"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' COMPUTE QUANTILE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Return inverse standard normal cumulative probability
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative = PROB_NormalInvCDF(Probability)
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' RETURN SUCCESS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Exit before failure and error-handler blocks
        Exit Function
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' FAIL - NUMERIC
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fail_Num:
    'Write diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, FailMsg
    'Return worksheet numeric error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative = CVErr(xlErrNum)
    'Exit before the error handler
        Exit Function
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ERROR HANDLER
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Err_Handler:
    'Write unexpected runtime errors to diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, "Unexpected error in K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative: " & Err.Description
    'Return worksheet value error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative = CVErr(xlErrValue)
End Function


Public Function K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability( _
    ByVal LowerZ As Double, _
    ByVal UpperZ As Double, _
    Optional ByRef Status As String = "") _
    As Variant
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns P(LowerZ <= Z <= UpperZ) for the standard normal distribution.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   Interval (band) probabilities are used for confidence-region masses,
'   two-sided tail budgeting and probability-of-touching style calculations.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   NORM.S.DIST(UpperZ, TRUE) - NORM.S.DIST(LowerZ, TRUE).
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Difference of standard normal CDFs (Hart/West). Not proprietary.
'
' INPUTS
'   LowerZ
'     Lower standard-normal bound.
'
'   UpperZ
'     Upper standard-normal bound.
'     Must be greater than or equal to LowerZ.
'
'   Status
'     Optional ByRef diagnostic message.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double interval probability in [0, 1].
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates finite bounds and UpperZ >= LowerZ.
'   - Returns NormalCDF(UpperZ) - NormalCDF(LowerZ).
'   - Clamps a tiny negative rounding residual to 0.
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Invalid or reversed bounds return CVErr(xlErrNum).
'   - Unexpected runtime errors return CVErr(xlErrValue).
'   - Detailed diagnostic messages are written to Status (status bar only when
'     PROB_WRITE_STATUS_BAR is True).
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - PROB_IsFinite
'   - PROB_NormalCDF
'   - PROB_SetStatus
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-08
'==============================================================================
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' DECLARE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Dim Probability         As Double          'Interval probability
    Dim FailMsg             As String          'Detailed failure message
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' INITIALIZE
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Route unexpected runtime errors to the error handler
        On Error GoTo Err_Handler
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Initialize the failure message buffer
        FailMsg = vbNullString
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VALIDATE INPUTS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Validate finite bounds
        If Not PROB_IsFinite(LowerZ) Then
            FailMsg = "LowerZ must be a finite number"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If

        If Not PROB_IsFinite(UpperZ) Then
            FailMsg = "UpperZ must be a finite number"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If
    'Validate ordering
        If UpperZ < LowerZ Then
            FailMsg = "UpperZ must be greater than or equal to LowerZ"
            GoTo Fail_Num
        End If
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' COMPUTE INTERVAL PROBABILITY
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Difference of cumulative probabilities
        Probability = PROB_NormalCDF(UpperZ) - PROB_NormalCDF(LowerZ)
    'Clamp tiny negative rounding residual
        If Probability < 0# Then Probability = 0#
    'Return interval probability
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability = Probability
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' RETURN SUCCESS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Clear diagnostic status
        PROB_SetStatus Status, vbNullString
    'Exit before failure and error-handler blocks
        Exit Function
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' FAIL - NUMERIC
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fail_Num:
    'Write diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, FailMsg
    'Return worksheet numeric error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability = CVErr(xlErrNum)
    'Exit before the error handler
        Exit Function
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' ERROR HANDLER
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Err_Handler:
    'Write unexpected runtime errors to diagnostics
        PROB_SetStatus Status, "Unexpected error in K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability: " & Err.Description
    'Return worksheet value error
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_IntervalProbability = CVErr(xlErrValue)
End Function


Public Function K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast( _
    ByVal Probability As Double) _
    As Double
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns the inverse standard normal cumulative distribution function using a
'   fast Double-to-Double contract.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   Monte Carlo engines transform large volumes of uniform random numbers into
'   standard-normal shocks. This routine avoids the overhead of a worksheet-
'   facing Variant/CVErr interface.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   None. This is a numerical helper, not a worksheet function.
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Raw Peter J. Acklam rational approximation (public), via the shared kernel
'   PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw in M_STATS_CORE. The Halley refinement
'   used by the worksheet-facing inverse is deliberately NOT applied here: for
'   Monte Carlo the ~1.15E-9 relative error is far below sampling error and the
'   unrefined kernel is materially faster.
'
' INPUTS
'   Probability
'     Probability level.
'     Expected to be strictly between 0 and 1.
'
' RETURNS
'   Double
'     Standard-normal quantile.
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Clips Probability away from 0 and 1 as a defensive safeguard.
'   - Calls the raw (unrefined) inverse-normal numerical kernel.
'   - Does not write to the Excel status bar.
'   - Does not return CVErr.
'
' ERROR POLICY
'   - Intended for validated numerical callers.
'   - Endpoint values are clipped rather than rejected.
'   - Public worksheet-facing validation remains the responsibility of
'     K_STATS_Normal_InverseCumulative or K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulative.
'
' DEPENDENCIES
'   - PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw   (M_STATS_CORE)
'   - PROB_EPS               (M_STATS_CORE)
'
' CALLED FROM
'   - Monte Carlo engines
'   - VBA numerical routines
'
' UPDATED
'   2026-07-08
'==============================================================================
'
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' NORMALIZE PROBABILITY
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Clip probability away from singular endpoints
        If Probability <= 0# Then Probability = PROB_EPS
        If Probability >= 1# Then Probability = 1# - PROB_EPS
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' RETURN RESULT
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    'Return the raw inverse standard-normal quantile
        K_STATS_NormalStandard_InverseCumulativeFast = PROB_NormalInvCDFRaw(Probability)
End Function


Public Function K_STATS_Normal_Density( _
    ByVal X As Double, _
    Optional ByVal Mean As Double = 0#, _
    Optional ByVal StdDev As Double = 1#, _
    Optional ByRef Status As String = "") _
    As Variant
'
'==============================================================================
' K_STATS_Normal_Density
'------------------------------------------------------------------------------
' PURPOSE
'   Returns the normal probability density function at X.
'
' WHY THIS EXISTS
'   Many risk, pricing and statistical models require normal densities with a
'   configurable mean and standard deviation, not only the standard normal case.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   NORM.DIST(X, Mean, StdDev, FALSE)  (Excel 2010+).
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Closed-form normal density via standardization. Not proprietary.
'
' INPUTS
'   X
'     Evaluation point.
'
'   Mean
'     Distribution mean.
'
'   StdDev
'     Distribution standard deviation.
'     Must be strictly positive.
'
'   Status
'     Optional ByRef diagnostic message.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double density value.
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates finite X, Mean and StdDev.
'   - Validates positive StdDev.
