'   GBM terminal-value examples and probability calculations for positive risk
'   factors.
'
' WORKSHEET EQUIVALENT
'   LOGNORM.DIST(X, MeanLog, StdDevLog, TRUE)  (Excel 2010+); legacy
'   LOGNORMDIST(X, MeanLog, StdDevLog) (cumulative only). Note the native
'   functions return #NUM! for X <= 0 whereas this routine returns 0, which is
'   the mathematically correct left-tail value for a positive-support variable.
'
' PROVENANCE
'   Standard normal CDF (Hart/West) of the standardized log variate. Public.
'
' INPUTS
'   X
'     Evaluation point.
'     For X <= 0, the cumulative probability is 0.
'
'   MeanLog
'     Mean of Log(X).
'
'   StdDevLog
'     Standard deviation of Log(X).
'     Must be strictly positive.
'
' RETURNS
'   Variant
'     Success => Double cumulative probability.
'     Failure => CVErr(xlErrNum) or CVErr(xlErrValue).
'
' BEHAVIOR
'   - Validates MeanLog and StdDevLog.
'   - Returns 0 when X <= 0.
'   - Otherwise computes NormalCDF((Log(X) - MeanLog) / StdDevLog).
'
' ERROR POLICY
